## Description: What is it? (max 1,500 characters)

The Collective Intelligence Design Playbook guides you through the different stages of designing a collective intelligence "intervention". Collective intelligence is the enhanced capacity that is created when people work together, often with the help of technology, to mobilize a wider range of information, ideas and insights. Collective intelligence emerges when these contributions are combined to become more than the sum of their parts.

## Purpose: Why do we use this method or tool for R&amp;D? (max 1,500 characters)

We use the Playbook to design collective intelligence interventions.

## Summary: Describe in one sentence, what it is and what it does? (max 120 characters)

The Collective Intelligence Design Playbook helps you design and deliver collective intelligence projects.

## Instructions: How is it used for R&amp;D? What steps to follow?

The playbook is a guide in itself. It provides a number of canvases, decision trees, etc. to help guide you through the process.

## Requirements: What is needed to effectively use it for R&amp;D? (e.g. skills, conditions, inputs, resources)

While the guidelines and facilitation techniques are fairly straightforward, the core concept of collective intelligence requires some a basic understanding of participatory methods and data innovation.
